{"name":"Turn Undead","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 3rd level, exert control over the undead and some d&aelig;monic beings, causing them to flee and/or cower. <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">At 3rd level the shaman has 1st-level turning ability (TA 1). </span>Evil shamans can opt instead to compel the submission and service of these foul creatures. In either case, the shaman must do the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Stand before the undead (within 30 feet)</li>\n<li>Speak boldly a commandment whilst displaying a holy symbol</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The referee must cross-reference the shaman&rsquo;s <em>turning ability</em> (TA) with the <em>Undead Type</em> to determine the shaman&rsquo;s chance of success. The referee may ask the player to roll a d12 to determine the outcome, or the result may be fixed. The results are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">d12 score equal to/less than the number indicated: <strong>T (turned)</strong></span></li>\n<li>d12 score greater than the number indicated: <strong>NT (not turned)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Undead Turning Definitions:</strong><br>The following definitions apply to Table 13:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><strong>NT (not turned):</strong> the undead are beyond the shaman&rsquo;s power to affect.</span></li>\n<li><strong>T (turned):</strong> 2d6 undead are compelled to cower/flee for 1 turn unless attacked.</li>\n<li><strong>D (destroyed):</strong> 2d6 undead are exorcized/destroyed, crumbling to dust.</li>\n<li><strong>UD (ultimate destruction):</strong> 1d6+6 undead are exorcized/destroyed, crumbling to dust.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>N.B.: Shamans of above-average charisma (15+) are more commanding; hence, their chance-in-twelve of success is improved by one (+1); e.g., a 4-in-12 chance becomes 5-in-12 (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>charisma</em>).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 33\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Frequency of Undead Turning:</strong> This ability can be used a number of times per day equal to the character&rsquo;s TA; however, the shaman can make but one attempt per encounter unless a second wave of undead arrive.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 13: Turn Undead</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p. 33]</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 34\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>How to Turn Multiple Undead Types:</strong> If multiple kinds of undead are met in a single encounter, only one d12 roll is required. The same result is applied to each <em>Undead Type</em>. Those of the lowest <em>Undead Type</em> are affected first, unless the sorcerer specifically targets a single creature, in which case only that creature potentially is affected (e.g., if a <strong>vampire</strong> stands at the fore of a pack of <strong>zombies</strong>, the shaman might step forth, holy symbol raised, and speak a commandment of abolishment, pointing a holy symbol directly at the <strong>vampire</strong>).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 34\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Evil Command of Undead:</strong> A shaman of Evil alignment may opt to exercise control over the undead on a successful <em>turn undead</em> check. Such undead remain under the sorcerer&rsquo;s sway unless <em>turned</em> or <em>commanded</em> by another sorcerer of equal or greater turning ability. Up to 2 HD of undead per TA level can be controlled. If a Neutral shaman attempts to <em>command undead</em>, then he or she will have turned to a darker path, submitting to Evil and no longer of Neutral alignment; consequences may ensue.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman 3+","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252111719,"modifiedTime":1681579139110,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"6BsZrCu0f4pbjNPu","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Magic Item Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 92\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Can utilize magic items normally restricted to clerics and magicians.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.faaU78MZepcdLvjA"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579139109,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"E1lRX1s6DPIeFUQb","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 92\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To decipher and invoke ecclesiastical and thaumaturgical scrolls containing spells that correspond to the shaman&rsquo;s chosen schools of sorcery, as included in the <strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Cleric-</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> or </span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Druid Spell List</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> (see </span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">, </span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Table 99</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> or </span><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">100</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">), and the </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><strong>Magician-</strong> or <strong>Necromancer Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 93</strong> or <strong>96</strong>).</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PLRVII62fOX22khR"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579139109,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"SR5VBR3ZiNCyUmqk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Harvest Venom","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 49\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To extract venom sacs from snakes, spiders, giant insects, and the like, should the opportunity present and appropriate containers be available. Shamans learn to dissect venomous creatures in the field. This skill is performed at a base 9-in-12 chance of success. If a <em>12</em> is rolled, a mishap occurs, and the shaman is exposed (e.g., eyes, nose, skin) to the poisonous fluid. For more information on the extraction of venom, see <strong>Chapter 9: Combat</strong>, <em>poison, venom harvesting</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":9,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NoxyIedR71kcOuQa"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579139109,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"WNZpBHGBynWypKXW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Longevity","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 79\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 11th level, ageing process slows. For every 13 years (1 Hyperborean cycle), the shaman effectively ages but 1 year.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman 11","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iPWkkv7WnyUR7Nbk"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250807770,"modifiedTime":1681579139109,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"YQZ352OQCpuk4pAM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Sorcery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 93\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>During character creation, the player must decide which two schools of magic their shaman casts. One choice is between cleric and druid spells; the other choice is between magician and necromancer spells. These spells are drawn from the <strong>Cleric-</strong> or <strong>Druid Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 99</strong> or <strong>100</strong>), and the <strong>Magician-</strong> or <strong>Necromancer Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 93</strong> or <strong>96</strong>). Spell school decisions are irreversible.</p>\n<p>The number and levels of spells cast per day are charted on <strong>Table 53</strong>, though shamans of high intelligence and high wisdom gain bonus spells cast per day (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>intelligence</em> and <em>wisdom</em>). For example, a 4th-level shaman with 13 intelligence and 13 wisdom can cast two level 1 spells and one level 2 cleric/druid spells per day, and two level 1 spells and one level 2 magician/necromancer spells per day.</p>\n<p>Shamans begin with knowledge of one level 1 cleric (or druid) spell. They also begin with a spell book, which may be in the form of thin stone tablets, bark sheets, animal skins, or shells laced together. At 2nd level, the shaman develops a level 1 magician (or necromancer) spell. Shamans develop one or more new spells at each level gain at the following schedule:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">1st level: &times;1 cleric/druid spell</span></li>\n<li>2nd level: &times;1 magician/necromancer spell</li>\n<li>3rd level: &times;1 cleric/druid spell</li>\n<li>4th level: &times;1 magician/necromancer spell</li>\n<li>5th level: &times;1 cleric/druid spell</li>\n<li>6th level: &times;1 magician/necromancer spell</li>\n<li>7th to 12th levels: &times;1 cleric/druid spell; &times;1 magician/necromancer spell</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 93\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>These spells are learnt automatically, with no need of qualification rolls, but they must be of castable levels (see <strong>Table 53</strong>). Developing new spells may include bonfire dancing, bone tossing, drumming or rattling, ice water immersion, or ritual sacrifice, during which the shaman may become temporarily possessed by a guiding spirit. Additional spells may be learnt outside of level training, but the process is more arduous (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>acquiring new spells</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252111719,"modifiedTime":1681579139109,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"dC0c5CxIPqiaSpbP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Draw Poison","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 40\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To draw and spit poison from a snakebite or another venomous wound, such as a scorpion sting or spider bite. The attempt must be made within 2 rounds of affliction for a 3-in-6 chance of success, within 4 rounds for a 2-in-6 chance of success, or within 6 rounds for a 1-in-6 chance of success. Success may revive one who has expired from poison, so long as a successful <em>trauma survival check</em> is made (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>constitution</em>). The deceased poison victim is restored to 0 hp, albeit at a price: permanent loss of 1 constitution point. N.B.: Victims of envenomed blades or ingested poison are beyond the shaman&rsquo;s aid.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579139108,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"faaU78MZepcdLvjA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Writing","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 32\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 93\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To scribe a known spell onto a scroll, creating a single-use magical device at a cost of 500 gp + 100 gp per spell level. Materials include the finest vellum, papyrus, rare bark, or animal skin; a fresh quill; and sorcerer&rsquo;s ink, such as sepia or the blood of a sacred animal. Alternatively, a shaman might sacrifice gems or jewellery of equal or greater value. Regardless, this involved process requires one week per spell level and must be completed on sacred ground.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5svHxLHi8sIn35Uj"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251303706,"modifiedTime":1681579139109,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"uT4ePuBdIflcEVHi","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Read Magic","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The ability to decipher otherwise unintelligible magical inscriptions or symbols placed on weapons, armour, items, doors, walls, and other media by means of the <em>sorcerer's mark</em> spell or other like methods.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251200032,"modifiedTime":1681579139109,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"xZGGiS7tCPCUz7xz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Totem","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 93\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The sacred symbol of kinship that a clan, tribe, family shares with an animal, plant, or another natural object. Ofttimes the clan is named after the totem; e.g., Clan of the Wolf or the Frog Tribe. Totemic emblems are carved from stone, ivory, and other media. Once per week, the shaman may beseech the totem spirit for wisdom and guidance as per the <em>contact otherworldly being</em> spell, but requiring half the monetary sacrifice.</p>\n<p>A shaman might view a totem as a brother, guardian, or protector. Dualism is a distinct possibility; meaning it is possible that the totem is speaking and acting, not the shaman. A totem might be transferred from one person to another through elaborate ceremony, inheritance, or expropriation.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.faaU78MZepcdLvjA"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579139110,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"zML5RwOhy4xKdwbk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Medicine Man","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 92\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To bind wounds, set sprains or broken bones, and concoct cures and antidotes for diseases and natural poisons, so long as the shaman has access to the herbs, roots, and ritualistic devices (e.g., drum, rattle) that are integral to shamanism. Gathering ingredients can be a time-consuming process, depending on circumstances. The process works as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Treat 1 person per day (including shaman) per level of experience; e.g., a 3rd-level shaman can treat up to three people per day.</li>\n<li>Process takes 1 turn to complete per person.</li>\n<li>Treatment involves the use of herbs, roots, and ritualistic dancing/percussion.</li>\n<li>Recipients immediately regain 1d4 hp and are stabilized if unconscious.</li>\n<li>Recipients can receive treatment only once per day.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Treating Poison/Disease</strong>: When treating a natural (plant or animal) poison or disease, the shaman has an 8-in-12 chance to devise an antidote if familiar with the affliction; if unfamiliar, chance of success is reduced to 4-in-12. In either case, the chance-in-twelve is increased by one (+1) if the shaman has 16+ wisdom. The shaman may attempt to treat a poison or disease but once per week. The process takes 1 turn to complete and is predicated on the intervention of an ancestral spirit.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"shaman","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.faaU78MZepcdLvjA"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679254261847,"modifiedTime":1681579139109,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"zx6zlyJZzdU7jgHO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
